  <h2>Don't wait it out — call now</h2>
  <p>Indoor temperatures in Wesley Chapel and Tampa Bay homes can climb from comfortable to unsafe in under two hours once the air conditioning stops. Infants, the elderly, anyone with respiratory conditions, and pets are at real risk. The first and most important thing to do: call <a href="tel:+18133952324">(813) 395-2324</a>. We'll get a licensed technician rolling while you handle the simple safety steps below.</p>

  <h3>Before our tech arrives — three things to check</h3>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mt-4">
    <li><strong>Thermostat.</strong> Make sure it's set to COOL and the setpoint is below the indoor temperature. Fresh batteries solve a surprising number of "emergencies."</li>
    <li><strong>Breaker panel.</strong> Look for a tripped air-handler or condenser breaker. Reset once — if it trips again immediately, stop and wait for us. That means a short.</li>
    <li><strong>Indoor air filter.</strong> A completely choked filter can freeze the coil and mimic an AC failure. If it's gray and fuzzy, replace it and switch the thermostat to fan-only for 1–2 hours to thaw the coil.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>What we bring on urgent no-cool calls</h2>
  <p>Our service vans leave Wesley Chapel loaded with the parts and tools that solve many Tampa Bay breakdowns on the first visit:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Capacitors (single and dual run) from 5 to 80 μF</li>
    <li>Contactors (24V coil, 30–50A)</li>
    <li>Condenser and blower fan motors across the common ECM and PSC sizes</li>
    <li>Universal thermostats (programmable and smart-compatible)</li>
    <li>R-410A and newer low-GWP refrigerants used in current equipment</li>
    <li>Condensate pumps, float switches, and drain-line flushing equipment</li>
    <li>Full digital manifold set, combustion analyzer, and thermal imager for rapid diagnosis</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Storm damage & hurricane season emergencies</h2>
  <p>Wesley Chapel and Tampa Bay's hurricane season runs June through November, and we respond to a wave of wind-damaged condensers and lightning-struck control boards every year. If your outdoor unit is bent, flooded, or was struck during a storm, <strong>do not try to restart it</strong> — water in the compressor or a damaged capacitor can turn into a fire hazard. Flip the disconnect at the unit, flip the breaker, and call us.</p>

  <h2>Prevent the next emergency with a maintenance plan</h2>
  <p>Over 70% of the emergency calls we run could have been caught in a 45-minute <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">spring or fall tune-up</a>. We offer preventive maintenance plans starting at modest monthly pricing that include priority dispatch during heat waves — if you're on a plan, you move to the front of the line.</p>

  <h2>Realistic scheduling across Tampa Bay</h2>
  <p>From our Wesley Chapel base, nearby communities like <a href="/service-areas/new-tampa-heating-and-cooling/">New Tampa</a>, <a href="/service-areas/land-o-lakes-hvac-services/">Land O' Lakes</a>, <a href="/service-areas/lutz-home-air-conditioning-service/">Lutz</a>, and <a href="/service-areas/wesley-chapel-ac-repair/">Wesley Chapel</a> are usually the quickest to schedule. Call now — we'll give you an honest ETA before dispatching.</p>
